Color, widescreen, stereo

Optional Swedish subtitles in separate idx/sub files.

Burton was born to play Henry VIII. If you have seen this Oscar-winning film from a TV channel, it has probably been edited to pieces in differenet pan-an-scan versions. Here, you will find the original extreme widescreen untouched, made from the 70 mm. original.

My new ripping procedure now produces decent quality for such a long film compressed into just 700 MiB.

DVDrip 2-pass, XviD
Widescreen 704x368, stereo sound AC3.
Burn tested, runs well in both my standalone DivX players.
